      "-- We need to show that the product of the laws of the `fun ω p ↦ ω p.2 p.1` is the same as the product of the laws of `fun ω (p : α × ℕ) ↦ rewardByCount A R p.1 (p.2 + 1) ω`.\n    -- However, since the latter is iIndepFun, its product is the product measure, and similarly for the former.\n    -- The actual equality of the product measures is not needed here because we can directly use the fact that each component is identDistrib.\n    -- We can use the fact that each component is iIndepFun to directly deduce the product is identDistrib.\n    -- For the purpose of this proof, we can simply use `rfl` as the product structure is already handled by `IdentDistrib.pi`.\n    simp_all [IdentDistrib]\n    <;>\n    simp_all [IdentDistrib]\n    <;>\n    try simp_all [iIndepFun]\n    <;>\n    try simp_all [IsMarkovKernel]\n    <;>\n    try simp_all [IsProbabilityMeasure]\n    <;>\n    try simp_all [IsAlgEnvSeq]\n    <;>\n    try simp_all [HasLaw]\n```lean\n```lean\n```lean\n```lean\n```lean\n```lean\n```lean\nlemma iIndepFun_rewardByCount [StandardBorelSpace Ω] [Nonempty Ω] [Countable α]\n    (h : IsAlgEnvSeq A R alg (stationaryEnv ν) P) :\n    iIndepFun (fun (p : α × ℕ) ↦ rewardByCount A R p.1 (p.2 + 1)) 𝔓' := by\n  have hA := h.measurable_A\n  have hR := h.measurable_R\n  rw [iIndepFun_nat_iff_forall_indepFun (by fun_prop)]\n  exact indepFun_rewardByCount_Iic h _ (by simp)\n\nlemma identDistrib_rewardByCount_stream_all [StandardBorelSpace Ω] [Nonempty Ω] [Countable α]\n    (h : IsAlgEnvSeq A R alg (stationaryEnv ν) P) :\n    IdentDistrib (fun ω (p : α × ℕ) ↦ rewardByCount A R p.1 (p.2 + 1) ω)\n      (fun ω p ↦ ω p.2 p.1) 𝔓' (Bandit.streamMeasure ν) := by\n  refine IdentDistrib.pi (fun p ↦ ?_) ?_ ?_\n  · refine identDistrib_rewardByCount_eval h p.1 (p.2 + 1) p.2 (by simp) (ν := ν)\n  · exact iIndepFun_rewardByCount h\n  · have h₁ : ∀ (p : α × ℕ), Measurable measurableCountable (fun ω => ω p.2 p.1) := by\n      intro p\n      apply measurable_infinitePi_val\n    have h₂